    "# <span style='color:DarkBlue'> Single Stock Tracker </span>  \n",
    "___\n",
    "\n",
    "The primary objective is to automate and enhance the analysis of any given stock by providing a versatile tool for historical data analysts. The script utilizes the Yahoo Finance API through the yfinance library to retrieve historical stock data, allowing users to specify the desired ticker symbol and time period for obtaining essential details such as Open, High, Low, Close, Volume, and Adjusted Close prices. Notably, the program is adaptable, enabling users to display historical data for their desired periods, thereby enhancing flexibility in analyzing stock performance. For the last year of historical data, the script offers advanced stock analysis features, including the calculation and visualization of Bollinger Bands for insights into stock volatility and potential trend reversals. Additionally, it identifies and displays support and resistance lines, aiding in the analysis of potential price levels where a stock may experience buying or selling pressure. Regular updates are conducted to ensure compatibility with the latest versions of relevant libraries, providing users with access to the most recent features and improvements for a comprehensive and up-to-date historical stock data analysis experience."
   ]
